# Generation pipeline simplicity

When improving own-engine generation quality, prefer fewer moving parts and stronger first-pass generation quality.

## Core principles

- Fewer layers beat more layers. If a fix can live in static prompt content or one deterministic data file, do not add another orchestration stage.
- The LLM is the builder, not a scaffold filler. Scaffolds should provide structure and safety, not pre-written identity.
- One-shot quality beats repair loops. Prevent recurring errors in system prompt guidance before adding more autofix logic.
- Keep widget/library safety centralized and explicit. Safe additions should be reflected consistently across capability inference, dependency completion, and toolkit guidance.
- Measure before adding complexity. If a repair rule rarely fires, prefer removing it and strengthening prompt-time instructions.

## Practical guardrails

- Prefer deterministic transforms over extra LLM repair passes.
- Keep dynamic context focused: prioritize high-signal blocks, trim repetitive boilerplate.
- Avoid introducing overlapping terminology; register new runtime terms in `docs/architecture/glossary.md` in the same change.
